  "monologue": "Using a small, protein-containing snack supports fullness and aligns with the user's preference for structure. The plan leverages urge logging and a short pause to counter evening cues, promoting gradual progress toward a steadier eating pattern without all-or-nothing shifts.",
  "utterance": "When evening hunger hits, try a small, protein-forward snack: one small apple with a tablespoon of almond butter. pause for about 5 minutes to check if the urge passes, then decide whether to have the snack or switch to a non-food cue. This keeps you within your structured routine and helps move toward steadier fullness with a manageable, portion-controlled choice.",
